{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2| }}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|msg=yes| }}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|msg=true| }}</nowiki>}}

URL2 handles formatting commonly found in the {{para|website}} parameter of an infobox:
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|[http://www.example.com]}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|http://www.example.com|website}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|{{URL|www.example.com}}}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|{{URL2|www.example.com}}}}</nowiki>}}

=== Same as Template:URL ===
The template wraps the output in {{tag|span|attribs=class="url"}} (see {{Section link||Microformat}}) and adds [[HTML element#wbr|&lt;wbr/&gt;]] before displayed periods:
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|www.example.com}}</nowiki>}}

The use of [[:en:HTTP|http://]], [[:en:HTTPS|https://]], a [[URL#prurl|protocol-relative URL]], or a different protocol is preserved in the URL but is not shown in the [[link text]]:
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|http://www.example.com}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|https://www.example.com}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|//www.example.com}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|ftp://ftp.example.com}}</nowiki>}}

If the path is only a slash (<code>/</code>) it is not displayed in the link text:
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|https://www.example.com/}}</nowiki>}}

The template also adds [[HTML element#wbr|&lt;wbr/&gt;]] before any displayed slashes (<code>/</code>) in the path:
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|https://www.example.com/path}}</nowiki>}}

For a URL containing an equal sign (<code>=</code>), use {{para|1}}:
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{URL2|1=http://www.example.com/path?section=17}}</nowiki>}}

== Microformat ==
The template wraps the ''displayed'' URL with <code>class="url"</code> so that it is included in any parent [[microformat]] which takes a URL parameter - see [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Microformats]].

== See also ==
* {{tl|URL}}
* {{ml|WikidataIB|url2}}
* {{tl|Official URL}}
* {{tl|Official website}}

